s. I might need to close it properly, and reflection might be required since the Log4j API doesn't close automatically.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering class definitions in packages**\\n\\nI’m wondering if it’s allowed to define a class in a package that's already defined, and it turns out it is, according to the loader. I need a child-first classloader with specific URLs, like log4jCoreJar and jmdnsLegacyJar. This loader should prioritize active classes and specifically handle `javax.jmdns.`, as it will load the old jar for that package. It's a bit tricky, but it seems like it should work!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_8s5MyIT9W7QQldlIRN7r3Fbx|fc_049dae7f6ec59baf016a0d8c151b708193868688acbca1ba70", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError\" -n tests/src | head -20"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1066, "output": 1712, "cacheRead": 28160, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 30938, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1779272700183, "responseId": "resp_049dae7f6ec59baf016a0d8bfcaa608193b0963939f6009782"}}
