n\nChanges:\n- Updated `tests/src/org.apache.logging.log4j/log4j-core/2.17.1/build.gradle`\n  - Changed legacy JmDNS dependency from `jmdns:jmdns:0.2` to `jmdns:jmdns:1.0`.\n    - `1.0` still uses the legacy version-1 API needed by `MulticastDnsAdvertiser`.\n    - It is less fragile than `0.2` around localhost initialization.\n  - Added a `jdk.net.hosts.file` system property at the Gradle `Test` task level so it is present before the forked test JVM starts.\n  - The generated hosts file maps the machine hostname to a non-loopback IPv4 address.\n\n- Cleaned up `MulticastDnsAdvertiserTest.java`\n  - Removed the late `@BeforeAll` hosts-file setup, since setting `jdk.net.hosts.file` after JVM startup was not reliable enough for `InetAddress` / legacy JmDNS initialization.\n  - Kept the isolated classloader test for the JmDNS v1 path.\n\nReason:\n- The previous fix set `jdk.net.hosts.file` too late, inside the test JVM.\n- Legacy JmDNS initializes through `InetAddress.getLocalHost()` during construction; if hostname resolution had already been cached or initialized, the test could still see loopback/invalid localhost behavior and return `null`.\n- Moving the hosts-file setup to Gradle makes the property available from JVM startup.\n\nI did not run the Gradle test command myself, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_049dae7f6ec59baf016a0d8dec541c8193801405e5dcfd3546\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2595, "output": 646, "cacheRead": 74752, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 77993, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1779273188794, "responseId": "resp_049dae7f6ec59baf016a0d8de585d08193bdb7d82a19cfce8a"}}
